Class RTSimulator

java.lang.Object
RTSimulator.RTSimulator
public class RTSimulator extends Object
Main class for RTSimulator application.

This class serves as the entry point for the RTSimulator application and provides static utility methods for debug output. It contains the main method that initializes the user interface.

Author:
ShiuJia

    • print

      public static void print(String message)
      Prints the specified message to standard output when DEBUG_MODE is enabled.

      This is a convenience helper used for lightweight debug output that should be suppressed when DEBUG_MODE is false.

      Parameters:
      message - the message to print; may be null

    • println

      public static void println(String message)
      Prints the specified message followed by a newline to standard output when DEBUG_MODE is enabled.

      Use this helper to emit a line of debug output. The newline emitted is the platform default supplied by System.out.

      Parameters:
      message - the message to print; may be null

    • println

      public static void println()
      Prints a blank line to standard output when DEBUG_MODE is enabled.

      Useful for separating blocks of debug output for readability.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Main method - entry point of the RTSimulator application.

      Logs startup information, attempts to initialize the user interface, and records success or failure using the class Logger.

      Parameters:
      args - the command line arguments (currently ignored)
